ent-RMCArmorPMCDirector-name = director's jacket
ent-RMCArmorPMCDirector-desc = A jacket that belongs to someone very important. It is made of insulating material and offers minor protection from all forms of damage.

ent-RMCArmorM4PMCEngineer-name = M4 pattern engineer PMC armor
ent-RMCArmorM4PMCEngineer-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Designed for high elemental protection, like shock, fire and fragments, lacks in terms of kevlar for bullet protection.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCCommando-name = M5X exoskeleton armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCCommando-desc = A complex system of overlapping plates intended to render the wearer all but impervious to small arms fire. A passive exoskeleton supports the weight of the armor, allowing a human to carry its massive bulk.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCSmartGunHarnessCommando-name = M5Xg exoskeleton gun operator armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCSmartGunHarnessCommando-desc = A complex system of overlapping plates intended to render the wearer all but impervious to small arms fire. A passive exoskeleton supports the weight of the armor, allowing a human to carry its massive bulk. This variant is designed to support ML66A Smart Gun.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCSmartGunHarness-name = PMC gun operator armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCSmartGunHarness-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Hooked up with harnesses and straps allowing the user to carry a ML66A Smart Gun.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCSynth-name = M4 pattern PMC synthetic armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCSynth-desc = A serious modification of the standard M3 armor. This variant was designed for PMC Support Units in the field, with every armor insert removed. It's designed with the idea of a high speed lifesaver in mind.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCSniper-name = M4 pattern PMC sniper armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCSniper-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Designed for high-profile security operators and corporate mercenaries in mind. This particular suit looks like it belongs to a high-ranking officer.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCLeader-name = M4 pattern PMC leader armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCLeader-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Designed for high-profile security operators and corporate mercenaries in mind. This particular suit looks like it belongs to a high-ranking officer.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCCorporate-name = M1 pattern corporate security armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCCorporate-desc = A basic vest with a We-Ya badge on the right breast. This is commonly worn by low-level guards protecting We-Ya facilities.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCLight-name = M4 pattern light PMC armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCLight-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Designed for high-profile security operators and corporate mercenaries in mind. Has some armor plating removed for extra mobility.

ent-RMCArmorM4PMCNoLight-name = M4 pattern PMC armor
ent-RMCArmorM4PMCNoLight-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Designed for high-profile security operators and corporate mercenaries in mind.

ent-CMArmorM4PMC-name = M4 pattern PMC armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMC-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Designed for high-profile security operators and corporate mercenaries in mind.

ent-RMCArmorM4PMCBulletProof-name = M4 pattern PMC bulletproof armor
ent-RMCArmorM4PMCBulletProof-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Designed for high-profile security operators and corporate mercenaries in mind. This set is designed for protecting against ballistics, and has minimal protection against blades and biohazards.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCCorporateLead-name = M1 pattern corporate security armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCCorporateLead-desc = A basic vest with a We-Ya badge on the right breast. This variant is worn by low-level guards that have elevated in rank due to 'good conduct in the field', also known as corporate bootlicking.

ent-RMCArmorM4PMCSynthFilled-name = M4 pattern PMC synthetic armor
ent-RMCArmorM4PMCSynthFilled-desc = A serious modification of the standard M3 armor. This variant was designed for PMC Support Units in the field, with every armor insert removed. It's designed with the idea of a high speed lifesaver in mind.

ent-CMArmorM4PMHeavy-name = PMC heavy armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMHeavy-desc = A modification of the standard M3 armor. Featuring additional plating and straps to provide superior protection.

ent-CMArmorM4PMCCommandoSurvivor-name = damaged MY7 pattern Commando armor
ent-CMArmorM4PMCCommandoSurvivor-desc = A modification of the W-Y PMC armor patterns. Designed for elite corporate mercenaries in mind. This one has a lot of scratches and acid damage.

